1 Section 1. Section 60-6,273, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska,
2 is amended to read:
3 60-6,273 Evidence that a person was not wearing an occupant
4 protection system or a three-point safety belt system at the time he or
5 she was injured is shall not be admissible in any civil proceeding for
6 purposes of determining: regard to the issue of liability
7 (1) Liability or proximate cause; and
8 (2) Mitigation but may be admissible as evidence concerning
9 mitigation of damages , except that it shall not reduce recovery for
10 damages by more than five percent.
11 Sec. 2. Original section 60-6,273, Reissue Revised Statutes of
12 Nebraska, is repealed.
